<h1 style="color:red;">ITEC1000A Assignment 1</h1>

<p>
This page is to illustrate the use of HTML (Hyper Text Markup Language) codes to create webpages that will also display the answers to this assignment. <br>
HTML is the standard markup language that is used to create webpages and therefore is a must-learn language for any information technology student. <br>
With HTML, images, links to other sites, or a link to an email can also be placed in the webpage. Knowing HTML fully will allow for a lot of creative <br>
webpages to be conjured up. As thisis still a new skill, it will take a lot of practice and understanding to make a webpage look much more presentable. <br>
<blockquote><img src="http://www.students.yorku.ca/~wkfc/itec1000/images/html_tatoo.jpg" alt="HTML Tatoo" align="middle"></blockquote><br>
A humourous picture depicting a person's structure as an html document. the end head tag meaning the head are of the human body has ended, and the body tag to 
describe the body part of the human begins.

